NAME
    Poet -- A flexible application environment

SYNOPSIS
        # In a module...
        use Poet qw($conf $env $log);

DESCRIPTION
    Poet provides a flexible environment for a web or standalone
    application. It gives you

    *   A standard root directory with conf, lib, bin, etc., autodetected
        from any script inside the environment

    *   A multi-file configuration layout with knowledge of different
        application "layers"

    *   Easy one-line access to environment, configuration, caching and
        logging objects

ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
    Poet was originally designed and developed for the Digital Media group
    of the Hearst Corporation, a diversified media company based in New York
    City. Many thanks to Hearst for agreeing to this open source release.
    Hearst has no direct involvement with this open source release and bears
    no responsibility for its support or maintenance.

AUTHOR
